snippet.textDisplay: I know all about the shedding thing.  There was a time when I have very long hair.  It was always a huge pain.  It took longer to wash, forever to dry, and the long hairs I shed were everywhere.  Sure, it was cool to have a pony tail that hung down between my shoulder blades, but in the summer (temps in in the 110 F and up range) it was nearly unbearable.  Never had any color done or 'fad' haircuts and I've always described it as Bronze colored, until it started going silver...
snippet.textOriginal: I know all about the shedding thing.  There was a time when I have very long hair.  It was always a huge pain.  It took longer to wash, forever to dry, and the long hairs I shed were everywhere.  Sure, it was cool to have a pony tail that hung down between my shoulder blades, but in the summer (temps in in the 110 F and up range) it was nearly unbearable. snippet.textDisplay: Me, someone who currently has colored hair: Jaiden why the heck would you take a shower the same day you get your hair dyed? Your hair would be washed at the salon as part of the dyeing process, so either take a shower the day before or if you really need to wash your body just put your hair up so it doesn't get wet. Otherwise you are just asking for it to stain and face quicker. Also they sell shampoo like products now to help hair stay colored for longer so that's cool. Sadly I can't remember what they are called for anyone who wants to get their hair dyed.
